-- Rosneftegaz May Buy Vekselberg’s Power Assets, Vedomosti Reports
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-28T04:03:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/rosneftegaz-may-buy-vekselberg-s-power-assets-vedomosti-reports.html
OAO Rosneftegaz, a Russian state-run
holding of which President  Vladimir Putin ’s ally  Igor Sechin  is
chairman, may buy power assets from billionaire  Victor
Vekselberg ’s ZAO Integrated Energy Systems,  Vedomosti  reported,
citing industry officials it didn’t identify.  Vekselberg’s company owns shares of utilities OAO TGK-5,
OAO TGK-6, OAO Volga TGK and OAO TGK-9 and has previously
considered merging its power assets with those of OAO Gazprom,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  